commitResults.messageTitle: Return exception message to display it in GUI
Throw exception if the save file is in the wrong String format
commitResults.messageBody:
The GUI would not load at all as to prevent the user from using the app.
If the app were to be used, how should the save file be loaded? Using a
new save file would delete all the data (which is undesirable), while
finding an exception at the start of the save file would also require
deleting all the data (anything after the problem). Thus, not loading
the GUI tells the user about the problem with save file and gives them
a chance to fix the save file.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add assert statements, mostly to prevent null pointer exceptions
commitResults.messageBody:
Parameters are checked to prevent such exceptions. clearData has a false
assertion to ensure that user data is not accidentally cleared. While
this leads to assertion errors in ListTest and StorageTest, there is
no easy way to clear the storage easily for the other tests.

Remove dead code, abstract each switch case into a method
commitResults.messageBody:
The methods used to abstract switch cases are private as they are only
used in the class itself. This helps to keep each method short so that
it is easier to trace through them. To reduce repetition, some methods
may not be fully suitable for some cases, but are used as long as they
are similar enough.
